---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Poesis is the company harnessing the generative AI era so that systems continuously develop on their own — created by Clément Cazaud."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="motto">Define the world in software; govern it.</p>
      <h1>We make definitions generate systems.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Poesis transforms organizations — IT first — through AI-generative, agentic capabilities grounded in systemic governance. We author the open standard, build the engine and application that run it, and deliver the transformation around them.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Positioning</p>
      <h2>Governance that systems can act on.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The definitions that systems are supposed to obey have lived in prose — fragmented across architecture wikis, compliance spreadsheets, and review boards that drift from reality. Poesis turns them into typed, versioned, machine-operable definitions, and ships the <a href="/sie">engine</a> and <a href="/itip">application</a> that put them to work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Team</p>
      <h2>The people behind Poesis.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The <a href="/standard">GSM</a> standard, <a href="/sie">SIE</a>, and <a href="/itip">ITIP</a> originate from a single thesis: systems should be <em>defined and governed</em>, not merely described. Today that thesis is carried by one person &mdash; for now.</p>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="margin-top:1.6rem">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="tag">Founder</span>
          <h3>Clément Cazaud</h3>
          <p>Enterprise &amp; solutions architect, software engineer, agentic AI expert, and systems thinker &mdash; and the business owner and products manager behind Poesis. Clément has spent his career turning sprawling IT landscapes into coherent, governed systems: mapping architectures, leading transformations, writing the code, and building the tooling that makes governance executable rather than aspirational. GSM, SIE, and ITIP grew out of that work &mdash; and out of the agentic AI era that now makes it tractable: the conviction that the definitions a system must obey belong in software, where they can be versioned, reasoned over, and generated from.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:.6rem"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/clement-cazaud" target="_blank" rel="noopener">See the full track record on LinkedIn →</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top:1.6rem"><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/contact">Get in touch →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
